SIMPLE: topless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Topless
<hw>Top"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having no top, or no
visble fop; hence, fig.: very lofty; supreme; unequaled.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧
The <xex>topless</xex> Apennines.⟦rdquo⟧ ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Topless</xex>
fortunes.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>wearing no clothes above the waist, said especially
of women.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>featuring entertainment by women wearing no clothes
above the waist; <as>as, a <ex>topless</ex> go-go joint</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Top-light</ent>⟦br⟧
